      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 59,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 17:59",
      "text": "the children of Saphatia, the children of Ettel, the children of Phacarath, the children of Sabaim, the children of Emim.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.17.60",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 60,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 17:60",
      "text": "All the Nathinim, and children of the servants of Solomon, were three hundred and ninety-two.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.17.61",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 61,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 17:61",
      "text": "And these went up from Thelmeleth, Thelaresa, Charub, Eron, Jemer: but they could not declare the houses of their families, or their seed, whether they were of Israel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.17.62",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 62,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 17:62",
      "text": "The children of Dalaia, the children of Tobia, the children of Necoda, six hundred and forty-two.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.17.63",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 63,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 17:63",
      "text": "And of the priests; the children of Ebia, the children of Acos, the children of Berzelli, for they took wives of the daughters of Berzelli the Galaadite, and they were called by their name.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.17.64",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 64,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 17:64",
      "text": "These sought the pedigree of their company, and it was not found, and they were removed as polluted from the priesthood.",
